Wash and dry all produce. Adjust #oven rack{} to middle and upper positions; preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Place @half chicken{24%ounce} skin-side up on a #baking sheet{}.
Sprinkle with @Fall Spice Blend{2%tsp}, @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a drizzle of
@vegetable oil{1%tbsp}; rub in to moisten. Tear @demi-baguette{1.5} into roughly
¾-inch pieces. Place on same sheet (use the rest as you like).

Place baking sheet in oven. Let roast until bread is crisp and golden,
~{6-7%minutes}. Remove baguettes from baking sheet and set aside. Return chicken
to oven on middle rack and roast until no longer pink in the thickest part of thigh,
~{35-45%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced).
Finely chop @celery{1}(finely chopped). Pick and chop @sage{1/4%ounce}(chopped)
leaves until you have 1 TBSP.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pan{} over medium heat (use an #ovenproof pan{}
if you have one). Add onion and celery. Cook until very soft, ~{6-8%minutes}.
Season with salt and pepper. Toss in @butter{1.5%tbsp}, chopped sage, and remaining
harvest spice. Cook, stirring, until butter is melted and herbs are fragrant,
about ~{30%seconds}.

Add baguettes and @dried cranberries{1%ounce}(Craisins) to pan and toss to combine.
Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2%ounce} and @water{1%cup}, tossing so that
liquid is absorbed. Season with salt and pepper. Cover with #foil{} and bake in
oven on upper rack for ~{15%minutes}.

> TIP: Transfer everything to a #baking dish{} first if your pan isn't ovenproof.

Toss @green beans{6%ounce}, a drizzle of oil, and a pinch of salt and pepper in a
#medium bowl{}. Spread out on baking sheet with chicken. Return to oven and roast
until beans are tender and chicken is done, ~{10-12%minutes}. Remove foil from
stuffing and continue baking until crisp on top, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Let chicken rest for a few minutes after removing from oven, then slice between
breast and leg to separate into two pieces (halve breast and divide leg to give
everyone both white and dark meat). Divide stuffing, green beans, and chicken
between plates and serve.